highlights.description: The importance of youth being taught skills to deal with their mental health.

While the circumstances of their stories are different, Mary's feelings from her story prompt Sara to think of a story where she experienced similar feelings of finding motivation when someone you trust says they don't believe in you.
Another story about being told that you don't have potential.
Encourages participants to use the stories/answers as a way to engage with one another.
Ebony and Tiana express similar experiences where family isn't necessarily the space for talking about mental health and emotions - seeking help outside the home.
Sharing similar feelings of responsibility as the family organizer which means there's little time for women to express their own feelings or emotions - shared experiences of guilt.
needing proximate voices in policy creation; ex. women & paid family leave
